Issue 1
Title: macOS 26.x / Swift 6.3.x: AES.GCM.open SIGTRAP on auth failure
Labels: bug, upstream, tier-1, crypto-core
Body:
AESGCMTests skips three tampering tests because CryptoKit's AES.GCM.open traps (signal 5) inside the framework on authentication failure for ciphertext-tampering and tag-tampering paths, before the throw can be caught. Reproduces standalone (no Aegis code involved). Affected: macOS 26.x with Swift 6.3.x toolchain.

Aegis behaviour is unaffected — same auth-failure path is verified by testDecrypt_tamperedAAD_throwsAuthenticationFailed which throws cleanly. Re-enable the three skips once Apple ships a fix or once we gain access to a workaround.

